{
  "stem": "9898.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And, oh, unforgettable-- the first night of Pesach, the first Seder-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] but before I tell you about this, we had spies, Jewish spies on the Aryan side.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the German knew that they wouldn't get us out so simple.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They'll have to fight.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they told us how they prepared, the German.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "What they had against us is 2,000 SS soldiers.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Listen to this-- three detachments of artillery; one thousand of German police; one thousand of Polish police; and one thousand of Ukrainians, Lithuanians, Latvians, and Estonians in the black uniforms, the supporting police.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Against them, we were 700 in the Jewish Fighting Organization and 300 in the other organization.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But the Germans knew we will come-- we won't come easy.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And on the first Seder, on April 19, 1943, we got a note-- calls from the other side.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The Germans are surrounding the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So immediately, everybody went to the bunkers.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And me, I have some medicine.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What medicine did I have?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Aspirin and nothing else, but-- and some material, you know, for worms.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And all the soldiers went to their posts.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And on the 19th in the morning, I'll show you on that-- my drawings there-- through the Muranowska gate, next to the Umschlagplatz, a platoon of German soldiers came through the Muranowska Street into the ghetto, and went to Muranowska Square, singing, you know, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the Northern people, the Ubermenschen, Supermenschen-- singing, happy.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, when they came in Muranowska Street, there were two buildings there with flags, one Jewish flag, with the Magen David, and one Polish flag.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The boys-- the Jewish boys knew, that every bullet has to kill.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Otherwise, they wouldn't come out.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
